description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an H&amp;I Administrative Officer to provide efficient and effective administrative support to the H&amp;I Department to facilitate the timely provision of H&amp;I diagnostic services ensuring procedures in relation to donors and patients are carried out to the highest possible standard.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work as an active team member assisting with a comprehensive range of administrative duties/procedures as dictated by the workload of the Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is based in a laboratory and part of the role will involve unpacking blood samples and inputting patient identification into our databases.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to communicate with the general public, other NHSBT departments and external contacts as required, whilst maintaining strict confidentiality at all times and ensuring that information relating to patients and donors is kept in a manner in accordance with NHSBT policies &amp; procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The advert will close for applications at midnight on the evening of 15/11/2020 and interviews will be held on 25/11/2020, subject to confirmation. For informal enquiries please contact Jayne Johnson at jayne.johnson2@nhsbt.nhs.uk.&lt;/p&gt;
